<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="G1" checkit-title="Area">
    <statement>
        <p> A rectangle stands with it's longest side vertical and a triangle is attached cleanly to the bottom of the rectangle. The dimensions of the shape are as follows: the rectangle has base 7 and height 9 and the triangle has altitude 4, where everything is measured in feet.
            <ol>
                <li>Sketch a drawing of this situation to the best of your ability.</li>
                <li>Find the total area of this shape.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The volume is <m>A \approx 77.0</m> <m>ft^2</m>. This was computed using the formula <m>A = bh_1 + \frac{1}{2}bh_2</m>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
